model

Interface Vehicle

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractVehicle, Bicycle, Car, Human, Truck

    public interface Vehicle
    An interface for objects that can move in four directions.
    Version:
    Autumn 2014
    Author:
    Marty Stepp, Daniel M. Zimmerman, Alan Fowler (acfowler@u.washington.edu)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean canPass(Terrain theTerrain, Light theLight)
      Returns whether or not this object may move onto the given type of terrain, when the street lights are the given color.
      Direction chooseDirection(java.util.Map<Direction,Terrain> theNeighbors)
      Returns the direction this object would like to move, based on the given map of the neighboring terrain.
      void collide(Vehicle theOther)
      Called when this Vehicle object collides with the given other movable object.
      int getDeathTime()
      Returns the number of updates between this vehicle's death and when it should be revived.
      Direction getDirection()
      Returns this Vehicle object's direction.
      java.lang.String getImageFileName()
      Returns the file name of the image for this Vehicle object, such as "car.gif".
      int getX()
      Returns this Vehicle object's x-coordinate.
      int getY()
      Returns this Vehicle object's y-coordinate.
      boolean isAlive()
      Returns whether this Vehicle object is alive and should move on the map.
      void poke()
      Called by the UI to notify a dead vehicle that 1 movement round has passed, so that it will become 1 move closer to revival.
      void reset()
      Moves this vehicle back to its original position.

      Sets this object's facing direction to the given value.
